"""
Enterprise Permission Service for Two-Tier Identity.

This service provides permission checking for both platform (Ascend staff)
and tenant (customer) users, integrating with the existing RBAC system
while adding scope-based isolation.

Architecture:
    Platform Tier (Ascend Staff)
    ├── Super Admin: Full platform access
    ├── Support: Read-only platform + org metadata
    └── Billing: Billing operations only

    Tenant Tier (Customer Users)
    ├── Owner: Full organization access + billing
    ├── Admin: Full org access except billing
    ├── Approver: View + approve workflows
    ├── Operator: Create/manage resources
    └── Viewer: Read-only access

Usage:
    from services.permission_service import PermissionService

    permission_service = PermissionService(db)

    # Check permission
    allowed = await permission_service.has_permission(
        user=token_claims,
        resource="policies",
        action="create"
    )

    # Use decorator
    @require_permission("policies", "create")
    async def create_policy(...):
        ...
"""

